{{> _partials/base}}
{{!

    This is an example of a meta page, evey template except the class and package page
    is a meta page. It is rendered once and with full context of both packages and
    root classes. These pages can be used for creating indices and so on.

    Context of each meta page has two root values:
        - classes: a sorted list of root classes as ClassInfo objects
        - packages: a sorted list of all packages as PackageInfo objects

    Meta data contained in context are:
        - meta.pathToRoot: the path to root of the outputed HTML

}}
{{#*inline "content" }}

    <header>
        <h1>Classes</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="container">

        {{#each classes as |class| }}
            <div class="row">
                <br/>

                <h3>
                    <a href="{{meta.pathToRoot}}{{linkTo qualifiedName}}">{{qualifiedName}}</a>
                </h3>

                {{> _partials/class/class_visibility class=class }}

                {{> _partials/class/class_type class=class }}

            </div>
        {{/each}}

    </div>

{{/inline}}

